      "comment_id" : 119517790,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "However, you can use MAX_VALUE in many situations like a merge sort were it can be used as a &quot;sentinel value&quot;.  If for example, you wanted to return the smallest of a pair and you happened to compare the sentinel with the value 2147483647 occurring in your list.  It doesn&#39;t matter which you return."
