  "title" : "How to implement infinity in Java?",
  "body" : "<p>Does Java have anything to represent infinity for every numerical data type? How is it implemented such that I can do mathematical operations with it?</p>\n\n<p>E.g.</p>\n\n<pre><code>int myInf = infinity; //However it is done\nmyInf + 5; //returns infinity\nmyInf*(-1); //returns negative infinity\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>I have tried using very large numbers, but I want a proper, <strong>easy</strong> solution.</p>\n"
